&lt;Spectrum Concepts Inc> said itunveiled a new software product called XCOM 6.2 that linksvarious computer systems together.    The company said the software can transfer data betweenInternational Business Machine Corp's &lt;IBM> mainframecomputers, System/38 minicomputers, Digital Equipment Corp&lt;DEC> Vax minicomputers, IBM personal computers and Token Ringlocal area networks.    It said prices range from 26,000 dlrs for a mainframelicense to 200 dlrs for each personal computer. Reuter&#3;